1
00:00:32,332 --> 00:00:36,868
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>JAROD WAS A REAL</i>                
<i>EVEN-TEMPERED MAN.</i>              


2
00:00:36,936 --> 00:00:41,406
STAYED HERE FOR ABOUT A WEEK,   
THEN HE WAS GONE.               


3
00:00:41,475 --> 00:00:43,575
I SORT OF ACT AS                
BUILDING MANAGER HERE,          


4
00:00:43,644 --> 00:00:47,212
BUT MY REAL PASSION             
IS ACUPUNCTURE.                 


5
00:00:47,281 --> 00:00:49,414
<i>JAROD REALLY GOT INTO IT TOO.</i>   


6
00:00:49,483 --> 00:00:51,416
YOU STUCK NEEDLES INTO HIM?     


7
00:00:51,485 --> 00:00:54,786
<i>ACTUALLY, I TAUGHT HIM</i>          
<i>HOW TO DO IT HIMSELF.</i>           


8
00:00:54,855 --> 00:00:57,021
            FOR WHAT PURPOSE?   
STRESS REDUCTION.               


9
00:00:57,090 --> 00:01:01,059
    I'M VERY GOOD AT REDUCING   
    TENSIONS IN THE BODY.       


10
00:01:01,128 --> 00:01:04,596
    FUNNY. I'M VERY GOOD        
    AT CAUSING THEM.            


11
00:01:04,665 --> 00:01:08,933
JAROD WANTED THE NEEDLES PLACED 
ALONG THE BRACHIAL PLEXUS.      


12
00:01:09,002 --> 00:01:13,372
        <i> BRACHIAL PLEXUS?</i>       
        <i> NERVE CENTER FOR</i>       
        <i> THE UPPER EXTREMITIES?</i> 


13
00:01:13,441 --> 00:01:16,608
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>HE WANTED ME TO LEAVE THEM IN</i>   
<i>UNTIL HIS ARM WAS PARALYZED.</i>    


14
00:01:16,677 --> 00:01:18,643
            <i> HE'D WALK AROUND</i>   
            <i> LIKE THAT FOR DAYS.</i>


15
00:01:18,712 --> 00:01:20,812
YOU OBVIOUSLY LIVED             
THROUGH THE '60s.               


16
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:25,383
DOES YOUR COMPANION KNOW        
THE CONCEPT OF FREE LOVE?       


17
00:01:27,988 --> 00:01:31,389
    - WHEN DID HE LEAVE?        
    - TWO DAYS AGO.             


18
00:01:31,458 --> 00:01:36,127
    WELL, THEN OUR WORK HERE    
    IS MERCIFULLY DONE.         


19
00:01:36,196 --> 00:01:38,930
        OH.                     


20
00:01:38,999 --> 00:01:41,165
BUT THEN YOU'LL                 
MISS OUT ON THIS.               


21
00:01:44,404 --> 00:01:46,405
HE SAID YOU'D KNOW              
WHAT IT MEANT.                  


22
00:02:00,154 --> 00:02:02,487
    THIS BUILDING               
    ISN'T FAR FROM HERE.        


23
00:02:02,556 --> 00:02:04,556
                        HMM.    


24
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:26,811
        [ Chattering ]          


25
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:29,147
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>HE'S UP THERE.</i>                  
<i>[ Sirens Wailing ]</i>              


26
00:02:32,886 --> 00:02:35,453
WHERE THE HELL'S                
MY CAMERAMAN?                   


27
00:02:38,458 --> 00:02:41,293
        IT'S A LONG WAY DOWN.   
STAY AWAY FROM ME.              


28
00:02:41,361 --> 00:02:43,562
STAY AWAY FROM ME.              
            I JUST WANT         
            TO TALK TO YOU.     


29
00:02:43,631 --> 00:02:45,630
JAROD, WHAT THE HELL            
ARE YOU DOING UP THERE?         


30
00:02:45,698 --> 00:02:47,999
<i>YOU'D BETTER BE</i>                 
<i>ROLLING ON THIS GUY.</i>            


31
00:02:49,436 --> 00:02:51,803
            <i> MY NAME'S JAROD.</i>   
            <i> WHAT'S YOUR NAME?</i>  


32
00:02:52,806 --> 00:02:55,474
        DAVE. MY NAME'S DAVE.   


33
00:02:55,542 --> 00:03:00,045
<i>BEAUTIFUL FAMILY.</i>               
<i>I'M GUESSING THAT'S YOUR WIFE</i>   
<i>AND YOUR CHILDREN.</i>              


34
00:03:01,148 --> 00:03:03,148
        THEY'RE GONE.           


35
00:03:03,217 --> 00:03:06,184
    THEY WERE EVICTED,          
    AND NOW I CAN'T FIND THEM.  


36
00:03:06,253 --> 00:03:09,688
<i>DAVE, I'M SURE THEY'RE FINE.</i>    


37
00:03:09,757 --> 00:03:11,890
I'LL BET THEY'RE OUT THERE      
SOMEWHERE WORRYING ABOUT YOU.   


38
00:03:11,959 --> 00:03:14,326
    NOBODY'S WORRIED ABOUT ME.  


39
00:03:14,394 --> 00:03:17,262
            IF THAT WERE TRUE,  
            WOULD I BE UP HERE  
            ON THIS LEDGE?      


40
00:03:17,330 --> 00:03:19,764
        <i> I'M SURE THAT THEY</i>     
        <i> ARE LOOKING FOR YOU.</i>   


41
00:03:19,833 --> 00:03:22,600
<i>WHY SHOULD THEY?</i>                
<i>I DRINK SOME.</i>                   


42
00:03:22,669 --> 00:03:24,602
    I CAN'T HOLD A JOB.         


43
00:03:24,671 --> 00:03:27,205
<i>I'VE LOST THEM FOR GOOD.</i>        


44
00:03:27,273 --> 00:03:30,908
<i>I CAN HELP YOU FIND THEM, DAVE.</i> 
<i>USE THE CAMERA.</i>                 


45
00:03:30,977 --> 00:03:33,445
            TELL THEM HOW MUCH  
            YOU LOVE THEM,      


46
00:03:33,513 --> 00:03:36,914
        HOW MUCH YOU MISS THEM, 
         HOW MUCH YOU NEED THEM.


47
00:03:36,983 --> 00:03:40,352
        <i> BUT FIRST, WE HAVE TO</i>  
        <i> GET OFF THIS LEDGE.</i>    


48
00:03:41,622 --> 00:03:43,989
                GRAB MY HAND.   


49
00:03:46,927 --> 00:03:50,429
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


50
00:04:33,540 --> 00:04:36,541
        [ Chattering ]          


51
00:04:39,012 --> 00:04:40,945
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>GRAB MY HAND.</i>                   


52
00:04:41,015 --> 00:04:43,415
<i>ONLY THING WOULD'VE MADE</i>        
<i>THIS BETTER WAS IF THE JUMPER</i>   
<i>WAS A TOPLESS DANCER.</i>           


53
00:04:43,484 --> 00:04:46,351
        - [ Laughs ]            
        - POOR GUY.             


54
00:04:46,419 --> 00:04:48,686
    <i> ANNIE, EDIT OUT SOME CLIPS</i> 
    <i> FOR THE PROMO TEAM A.S.A.P.</i>


55
00:04:48,755 --> 00:04:52,557
    THIS RUNS TONIGHT.          
    WE GOTTA GET SOME FOOTAGE OF
    THIS LOSER'S WIFE AND KIDS. 


56
00:04:52,626 --> 00:04:54,459
    <i> MAYBE THEY'VE CHECKED INTO</i> 
    <i> A HOMELESS SHELTER.</i>        


57
00:04:54,528 --> 00:04:57,061
    <i> AFTER ALL THIS,</i>            
    <i> DON'T YOU THINK THE FAMILY</i> 
    <i> DESERVES A LITTLE PRIVACY?</i> 


58
00:04:57,130 --> 00:05:00,465
    <i> PRIVACY? TO GET HER FACE</i>   
    <i> ON THE 10:00 NEWS AND SOME</i> 
    <i> PARTY MONEY IN HER POCKET,</i> 


59
00:05:00,534 --> 00:05:02,400
        THIS GUY'S WIFE'LL JUMP 
        AT THE CHANCE.          


60
00:05:02,469 --> 00:05:04,903
    - NO PUN INTENDED, HUH?     
    - [ Men Laugh ]             


61
00:05:04,972 --> 00:05:07,104
    TOO BAD YOU GOT SUCH        
    A GOOD GRIP THERE, JAROD.   


62
00:05:07,173 --> 00:05:10,642
    - WHY IS THAT?              
    - A HEROIC ATTEMPT          
      IS AS GOOD AS A SAVE.     


63
00:05:10,711 --> 00:05:13,545
    <i> THE PLUNGE WOULD'VE GIVEN</i>  
    <i> THIS PIECE A BETTER PUNCH.</i> 


64
00:05:13,613 --> 00:05:15,747
    SPOKEN LIKE AN ANCHORMAN    
    WHO WANTS HIS ANCHOR BACK.  


65
00:05:15,816 --> 00:05:18,750
        YOU KNOW, JAROD,        
        IF MY INSTINCTS ARE AS  
        GOOD AS I KNOW THEY ARE,


66
00:05:18,819 --> 00:05:21,319
        YOUR FACE IS GOING TO   
        BE RUNNING IN EVERY     
        LIVING ROOM IN AMERICA. 


67
00:05:21,387 --> 00:05:23,321
ACTUALLY, I THINK IT            
WOULD PLAY BETTER...            


68
00:05:23,390 --> 00:05:25,790
IF PHIL GOT CREDIT FOR THE SAVE.


69
00:05:25,859 --> 00:05:29,094
    - WHAT?                     
    - I MEAN, HE'S THE TALENT.  


70
00:05:29,163 --> 00:05:32,330
<i>HE'S THE HERO THAT EVERYONE</i>     
<i>TUNES IN TO SEE EACH DAY,</i>       
<i>NOT ME.</i>                         


71
00:05:32,398 --> 00:05:36,434
<i>ONLY PROBLEM IS, OUR HERO</i>       
<i>WAS STANDING IN A PARKING LOT</i>   
<i>100 FEET BELOW THE ACTION.</i>      


72
00:05:36,503 --> 00:05:39,637
    - YES, I KNOW,              
      BUT YOU NEVER SAW MY FACE.
    - SO?                       


73
00:05:39,707 --> 00:05:41,573
<i>SO IF YOU CUT IN JUST AFTER</i>     
<i>I MAKE THE GRAB,</i>                


74
00:05:41,641 --> 00:05:43,941
WE USE ALL THE COVERAGE I SHOT  
BEFORE I GOT UP ON THE ROOF.    


75
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:46,644
<i>WE LAY IN PHIL'S VOICE-OVER,</i>    
<i>AND THEN WE TAG IT WITH...</i>      


76
00:05:46,713 --> 00:05:50,115
A PICKUP SHOT OF PHIL EXITING   
THE BUILDING WITH THE JUMPER.   


77
00:05:52,820 --> 00:05:56,188
WE'RE NOT LONG FOR A TWO-SHARE  
AND LAST PLACE WITH THAT KIND   
OF ATTITUDE. DO IT.             


78
00:05:56,256 --> 00:05:58,790
            BUT CHRIS, IT'S--   
<i>UNETHICAL?</i>                      


79
00:05:58,858 --> 00:06:00,992
            YOU HEARD ME.       
            MAKE PHIL A HERO.   


80
00:06:02,996 --> 00:06:07,131
    - I THOUGHT ONLY GOD        
      REWROTE HISTORY.          
    - GOD NEVER WON SWEEPS.     


81
00:06:11,104 --> 00:06:13,871
        <i> [ Miss Parker ]</i>        
        <i> BEAUTIFUL PART OF TOWN.</i>
<i>[ Sydney ] DANGEROUS.</i>           


82
00:06:13,940 --> 00:06:17,375
NO WONDER JAROD                 
LEFT THE NOTEBOOK               
WITH THE ACUPUNCTURIST.         


83
00:06:17,444 --> 00:06:20,278
HE DOESN'T WANT US DOWN HERE.   
                COME ON, SYDNEY.
                WE'RE HERE.     


84
00:06:20,347 --> 00:06:22,380
        LET'S SEE IF RATBOY     
        LEFT ANYTHING BEHIND.   


85
00:06:38,097 --> 00:06:40,832
            THIS IS FUTILE.     
            JAROD'S LONG GONE.  


86
00:06:41,835 --> 00:06:43,768
AFRAID OF THE DARK, SYD?        


87
00:06:43,837 --> 00:06:46,137
        ONLY WHEN I             
        CAN'T SEE WHAT'S IN IT. 


88
00:06:46,205 --> 00:06:48,206
<i>[ Clatter ]</i>                     


89
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:52,744
                        DAMN IT.
                    <i> [ Clatter ]</i>


90
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:58,649
MISS PARKER, MAYBE WE SHOULD    
GET THE CLEANUP TEAM            
TO CHECK THIS PLACE OUT.        


91
00:06:58,719 --> 00:07:00,585
                FORGET IT, SYD. 


92
00:07:00,653 --> 00:07:05,323
    I'D TRADE A DOZEN FERRAGAMOS
    FOR ONE JAROD ANY DAY.      


93
00:07:17,537 --> 00:07:19,737
<i>[ Object Clangs ]</i>               


94
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:23,041
I'M COUNTING TO THREE.          


95
00:07:23,110 --> 00:07:26,544
THEN I'M GONNA SHOOT            
WHOEVER YOU ARE.                


96
00:07:26,613 --> 00:07:29,114
    ONE,                        


97
00:07:29,183 --> 00:07:31,183
    TWO--                       


98
00:07:31,251 --> 00:07:33,251
<i>THREE!</i>                          


99
00:07:35,022 --> 00:07:39,090
    - WHAT DO YOU WANT?         
    - WHAT YOU GOT?             


100
00:07:39,159 --> 00:07:41,626
        I HAVE A NINE MILLIMETER
        IN YOUR FACE,           


101
00:07:41,695 --> 00:07:43,628
            AND YOU APPEAR      
            TO HAVE A KNIFE--   


102
00:07:43,697 --> 00:07:46,565
                A RUSTY KNIFE.  


103
00:07:48,034 --> 00:07:51,736
        <i> OH, YOU MUST BE FEELING</i>
        <i> LUCKY TODAY.</i>           


104
00:07:51,805 --> 00:07:53,438
    -<i> [ Glass Shatters ]</i>        
    -<i> [ Sydney Shouts ]</i>         


105
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:56,641
[ Groaning ]                    


106
00:08:00,547 --> 00:08:02,480
                    [ Chuckles ]


107
00:08:03,783 --> 00:08:07,752
            ARE YOU FEELING     
            LUCKY TODAY, HMM?   


108
00:08:07,821 --> 00:08:10,121
<i>GET THEIR WALLETS AND JEWELRY</i>   
<i>AND LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.</i>      


109
00:08:18,031 --> 00:08:21,032
    <i> [ Keyboarding ]</i>            


110
00:08:22,169 --> 00:08:24,802
WRITING PHIL'S COPY FOR HIM TOO?


111
00:08:24,871 --> 00:08:28,639
    I'M JUST TRYING TO SEND     
    A MESSAGE TO AN OLD FRIEND. 


112
00:08:30,977 --> 00:08:32,844
    <i> SO YOU THINK I WAS WRONG,</i>  


113
00:08:32,912 --> 00:08:36,014
        LETTING PHIL TAKE CREDIT
        FOR SAVING THE JUMPER.  


114
00:08:36,082 --> 00:08:38,483
AS OUR NEW, ESTEEMED            
NEWS DIRECTOR ALWAYS REMINDS ME,


115
00:08:38,552 --> 00:08:40,919
I GET PAID TO CUT TAPE,         
NOT TO THINK.                   


116
00:08:40,987 --> 00:08:43,754
        FROM WHAT I UNDERSTAND, 
        YOU WIN AWARDS DOING IT.


117
00:08:45,091 --> 00:08:48,193
WELL, AWARDS DON'T COUNT        
FOR MUCH AROUND HERE.           


118
00:08:48,261 --> 00:08:51,996
PULITZER'S ROLLING OVER         
IN HIS GRAVE, AND NIELSEN'S     
PACKING DOWN THE DIRT.          


119
00:08:52,065 --> 00:08:55,734
    PHIL HAS ASKED ME TO GO OVER
    SOME OF HIS OLD FOOTAGE...  


120
00:08:55,802 --> 00:08:57,802
            TO SEE HOW HE LIKES 
             TO BE SHOT.        


121
00:08:59,406 --> 00:09:01,639
        DO YOU THINK MAYBE      
        YOU COULD SHOW ME       
        SOME OF HIS OLD TAPES?  


122
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:03,708
YEAH.                           


123
00:09:11,217 --> 00:09:13,885
SECOND SHELF.                   
            GREAT. THANK YOU.   


124
00:09:17,491 --> 00:09:20,759
    THE KEN WATANABE SHOOTING.  
    I HEARD ABOUT THIS.         


125
00:09:20,827 --> 00:09:22,927
        SO HAS HALF THE WORLD.  


126
00:09:22,996 --> 00:09:26,197
AND OUR IVY LEAGUE HITLER       
WAS PISSED WE DIDN'T            
HOOK THE OTHER HALF.            


127
00:09:26,266 --> 00:09:29,267
    IT'S CHRIS'S JOB            
    TO KNOW WHAT PEOPLE WANT,   


128
00:09:29,336 --> 00:09:31,836
    AND IT'S OUR JOB TO         
    MAKE SURE THEY GET IT.      


129
00:09:31,905 --> 00:09:36,207
WHICH DOESN'T MEAN WE SHOULD    
THROW OUT ANYTHING RESEMBLING   
JOURNALISTIC INTEGRITY.         


130
00:09:36,276 --> 00:09:38,209
IF IT BLEEDS, IT LEADS.         


131
00:09:38,278 --> 00:09:40,344
    THAT'S THE NEW WAVE         
    OF THE NEWS, ANNIE,         
    LIKE IT OR NOT.             


132
00:09:40,413 --> 00:09:44,015
WE EITHER SURF ALONG WITH IT,   
OR WE GET TORN APART            
IN THE RIPTIDE.                 


133
00:09:46,719 --> 00:09:48,653
<i>[ Annie ]</i>                       
<i>IT'S REALLY AN ACT.</i>             


134
00:09:48,721 --> 00:09:52,023
PHIL ACTUALLY WORSHIPS CRONKITE 
IN SECRET MIDNIGHT RITUALS.     


135
00:09:52,092 --> 00:09:54,125
                        HMM.    


136
00:09:54,194 --> 00:09:56,194
                WHO'S CRONKITE? 


137
00:09:57,530 --> 00:10:00,164
YOU'RE GONNA FIT IN             
JUST FINE HERE.                 


138
00:10:04,337 --> 00:10:07,905
    TONIGHT, EXCLUSIVELY        
    ON SEATTLE'S CHANNEL 43,    


139
00:10:07,974 --> 00:10:10,107
    OUR CONTINUING SERIES       
    ON LOCAL GANGS.             


140
00:10:10,176 --> 00:10:14,012
<i>IN THIS SHOCKING FOOTAGE,</i>       
<i>OUR OWN CAMERAMAN, KEN WATANABE,</i>


141
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:16,448
<i>CAPTURED ON VIDEOTAPE</i>           
<i>A GANG GATHERING...</i>             


142
00:10:16,516 --> 00:10:18,816
AT THE NORTH PUGET DOCK AREA.   


143
00:10:18,885 --> 00:10:22,320
    BUT WHAT HAPPENED NEXT      
    TOOK US BOTH BY SURPRISE.   


144
00:10:22,389 --> 00:10:24,388
    OUT OF NOWHERE,             
    THE 15th STREET BLEEDERS... 


145
00:10:24,457 --> 00:10:26,390
        CRASHED THE TURF        
        OF THE BURNS,           


146
00:10:26,459 --> 00:10:28,826
    LEADING TO                  
    AN EXPLOSIVE CONFLICT--     


147
00:10:28,895 --> 00:10:31,296
    A CONFLICT IN WHICH ONE OF  
    OUR OWN BECAME A CASUALTY.  


148
00:10:31,364 --> 00:10:34,031
        OH, GOD, I'M HIT.       
         OH, GOD. OH, GOD.      
        [ Gunfire ]             


149
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:37,402
PHIL, WHERE ARE YOU?            
 PHIL, I'M HIT. I'M HIT, MAN.   


150
00:10:37,471 --> 00:10:40,404
<i>MY ARM. MY ARM.</i>                 
<i>I CAN'T MOVE MY ARM.</i>            
<i>GET ME OUT OF HERE, MAN.</i>        


151
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:42,273
            GET ME OUT OF HERE. 
COME ON. COME ON.               


152
00:10:42,342 --> 00:10:45,609
<i>COME ON. GET UP.</i>                


153
00:10:45,678 --> 00:10:48,545
    TONIGHT, OUR PRAYERS        
    ARE WITH KEN WATANABE,      


154
00:10:48,614 --> 00:10:50,547
A COURAGEOUS YOUNG CAMERAMAN.   


155
00:10:50,616 --> 00:10:52,383
    GOD BLESS YOU, KEN.         


156
00:10:52,452 --> 00:10:57,155
<i>PHIL CAMPBELL,</i>                  
CHANNEL 43 NEWS,<i> AT 10:00.</i>      


157
00:11:53,212 --> 00:11:58,883
<i>DEHLILA, I THINK ABOUT YOU</i>      
<i>SO MUCH, MY BRAIN HURTS.</i>        


158
00:11:58,952 --> 00:12:02,720
I HAVE TO MEET YOU,             
TO SEE YOU.                     


159
00:12:04,724 --> 00:12:07,191
        -<i> [ Phone Rings ]</i>       
        - SAMSON.               


160
00:12:07,260 --> 00:12:09,193
I MEAN, BROOTS.                 


161
00:12:10,363 --> 00:12:13,731
        MR. PARKER?             
        UH, MR. PARKER, SIR.    


162
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:17,101
    HOW-HOW CAN I HELP YOU, SIR?


163
00:12:17,170 --> 00:12:22,140
    UH-- UH, NO.                
    NO, SIR, I HAVEN'T SEEN YOUR
    DAUGHTER SINCE YESTERDAY.   


164
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:24,575
                SYDNEY NEITHER. 
                I MEAN, EITHER. 


165
00:12:27,013 --> 00:12:30,381
Y-YES, SIR.                     
I'LL GET ON IT RIGHT AWAY, SIR. 


166
00:12:30,449 --> 00:12:32,716
YEAH, WELL,                     
IT'S A PLEASURE TALK-- TALK--   
            [ Click, Dial Tone ]


167
00:12:32,786 --> 00:12:35,319
                HELLO? HELLO?   


168
00:12:46,433 --> 00:12:50,134
            <i> - JAROD!</i>           
            <i> - DAVE?</i>            


169
00:12:50,202 --> 00:12:52,236
                YOU LOOK GREAT. 


170
00:12:52,304 --> 00:12:55,273
A STEP AT A TIME.               
THAT'S WHAT THEY TELL ME.       


171
00:12:55,341 --> 00:12:57,541
I JUST CAME BY TO SAY THANKS.   


172
00:12:57,610 --> 00:12:59,644
OF COURSE,                      
THE WAY THAT STORY AIRED,       


173
00:12:59,712 --> 00:13:02,747
I DON'T KNOW IF I SHOULD THANK  
THAT REPORTER PHIL OR YOU.      
                    [ Laughs ]  


174
00:13:02,815 --> 00:13:06,717
    WELL, STRANGE THINGS        
    HAPPEN IN TV.               
    I'M GLAD YOU'RE DOING WELL. 


175
00:13:06,786 --> 00:13:09,487
I DON'T KNOW WHAT GOT INTO ME.  


176
00:13:09,556 --> 00:13:11,823
            DID YOU FIND        
            YOUR WIFE AND KIDS? 


177
00:13:11,892 --> 00:13:16,794
YEAH, BUT SHE                   
DOESN'T WANT ME BACK            
UNTIL I FIND A JOB, SO--        


178
00:13:16,862 --> 00:13:19,564
        I'LL KEEP MY EYES OPEN. 
YEAH.                           


179
00:13:19,633 --> 00:13:24,168
                WHAT DO YOU     
                KEEP LOOKING AT?
OH, THOSE WIRES THERE.          


180
00:13:24,237 --> 00:13:28,439
<i>IF THEY'RE PLANNING ON</i>          
<i>HOOKING UP THAT SATELLITE DISH</i>  
<i>TO THEM WIRES,</i>                  


181
00:13:28,508 --> 00:13:31,175
THEY'RE GONNA BLOW OUT THEIR    
ELECTRICITY IN NOTHING FLAT.    


182
00:13:31,244 --> 00:13:35,513
        YOU'RE AN ELECTRICIAN?  
NOPE. SATCOM GRUNT.             


183
00:13:35,582 --> 00:13:39,584
I WASN'T ANY BETTER             
AT JUMPING OUT OF AIRPLANES     
THAN I AM FROM BUILDINGS,       


184
00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:42,820
BUT I DO KNOW A WIRING PROBLEM  
WHEN I SEE ONE.                 


185
00:13:44,590 --> 00:13:48,426
HEY, THANKS AGAIN, REALLY.      


186
00:13:48,494 --> 00:13:51,295
                    GOOD LUCK.  
THANKS.                         


187
00:13:56,702 --> 00:14:00,338
PHIL, THESE PIECES              
ARE EXCELLENT.                  


188
00:14:02,608 --> 00:14:04,742
    TWENTY YEARS OF BROADCASTING
    WILL DO THAT.               


189
00:14:04,810 --> 00:14:07,612
I WAS ESPECIALLY IMPRESSED WITH 
THE KEN WATANABE SEGMENT.       


190
00:14:07,681 --> 00:14:11,448
I WAS WONDERING.                
IS THE RAW FOOTAGE              
LYING AROUND SOMEWHERE?         


191
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:13,450
I'D LOVE TO SEE                 
HOW IT WAS CUT TOGETHER.        


192
00:14:13,519 --> 00:14:15,853
            MOST OF THOSE TAPES 
            GET RECYCLED.       


193
00:14:15,921 --> 00:14:17,889
EVEN WITH A PIECE THIS GOOD?    


194
00:14:17,957 --> 00:14:22,359
    <i> YEAH, WELL, THE STATION</i>    
    <i> DIDN'T USE TO CHARGE ME</i>    
    <i> FOR PARKING EITHER.</i>        


195
00:14:22,428 --> 00:14:24,429
    YEAH, RIGHT.                


196
00:14:36,375 --> 00:14:38,809
        WAY TO GO, DAVE.        
<i>[ Chattering ]</i>                  


197
00:14:45,818 --> 00:14:49,020
            [ Grunting ]        


198
00:14:52,391 --> 00:14:56,426
            [ Pipes Clanking ]  


199
00:14:56,495 --> 00:14:59,697
            AS IF GETTING MUGGED
            WASN'T ENOUGH.      


200
00:14:59,766 --> 00:15:01,899
[ Weakly ]                      
YOU SHOT ME.                    


201
00:15:03,735 --> 00:15:06,437
I DID NOT SHOOT YOU.            


202
00:15:06,505 --> 00:15:08,505
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.             


203
00:15:08,573 --> 00:15:10,674
    I NEVER LIKED GUNS.         


204
00:15:10,742 --> 00:15:13,377
    I HOPE YOU'LL STOP          
    CARRYING YOURS NOW.         


205
00:15:13,446 --> 00:15:16,013
            [ Sighs ]           


206
00:15:19,652 --> 00:15:21,752
        YOU'RE BLEEDING AGAIN.  
[ Groans ]                      


207
00:15:21,821 --> 00:15:27,691
        I NEED SOMETHING ELSE   
        TO TIE THIS WOUND WITH. 
WHAT ABOUT THAT NECK SCARF?     


208
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:31,628
- IT'S ONE OF A KIND, SYDNEY.   
- [ Chuckles ]                  


209
00:15:31,697 --> 00:15:37,301
WHICH IS WHAT                   
MY GOOD LEG WILL BE             
IF WE DON'T STOP THE BLEEDING.  


210
00:15:47,113 --> 00:15:50,280
    [ Shuddering ]              


211
00:15:50,349 --> 00:15:52,282
    I'M SORRY.                  


212
00:15:52,351 --> 00:15:54,918
[ Groaning, Grunting ]          


213
00:15:54,987 --> 00:15:56,987
[ Sighs ]                       


214
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:03,727
    THANK YOU.                  
    <i> YOU'RE GOING INTO SHOCK.</i>   
    <i> YOU NEED TO BE WARM.</i>       


215
00:16:18,010 --> 00:16:20,010
                    OH, MY GOD. 


216
00:16:21,013 --> 00:16:23,013
            OH, MY GOD, SYDNEY. 


217
00:16:23,081 --> 00:16:26,783
<i>DON'T LOOK NOW, BUT WE ARE</i>      
<i>GROUND ZERO FOR DETONATION...</i>   


218
00:16:26,852 --> 00:16:29,486
        TO BRING THIS DUMP DOWN.


219
00:16:29,555 --> 00:16:32,022
        PLEASE TELL ME          
        THAT YOU TOLD SOMEONE   
        WHERE WE WERE GOING.    


220
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:37,660
                    [ Sighs ]   


221
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,200
            [ Cooing ]          


222
00:16:46,271 --> 00:16:48,205
        THERE'S SOMETHING       
        I DON'T UNDERSTAND.     


223
00:16:49,675 --> 00:16:51,841
    - WHAT'S THAT?              
    - WHERE ARE THE LITTLE ONES?


224
00:16:52,844 --> 00:16:54,778
<i>THE WHAT?</i>                       


225
00:16:54,846 --> 00:16:57,280
YOU ALWAYS SEE THE BIG PIGEONS, 
YOU KNOW, WITH THE SCARS...     


226
00:16:57,349 --> 00:16:59,783
        <i> AND THE BROKEN WINGS</i>   
        <i> AND THE MISSING LEGS.</i>  


227
00:16:59,852 --> 00:17:01,985
            <i> BUT YOU NEVER SEE</i>  
            <i> THE LITTLE ONES.</i>   


228
00:17:02,054 --> 00:17:05,322
I NEVER REALLY                  
THOUGHT ABOUT IT.               
                HEY, I KNOW YOU.


229
00:17:05,391 --> 00:17:07,892
        YOU'RE THE CAMERAMAN    
        THAT WAS ON THE NEWS.   


230
00:17:09,095 --> 00:17:13,297
                I'M JAROD CRANE.
    KEN.                        


231
00:17:13,366 --> 00:17:16,666
        THAT WAS INCREDIBLE     
        FOOTAGE YOU CAPTURED.   


232
00:17:16,735 --> 00:17:20,203
THANKS. I NEVER PLANNED ON      
BECOMING A STORY THOUGH.        


233
00:17:20,272 --> 00:17:22,640
    WHEN ARE YOU GOING          
    BACK TO WORK AT THE STATION?


234
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:25,542
<i>AND DO WHAT?</i>                    
<i>LOG COMMERCIALS?</i>                


235
00:17:26,612 --> 00:17:29,313
        I'M A SHOOTER, MAN.     


236
00:17:29,381 --> 00:17:32,615
    MY DAYS ON THE FRONT LINE   
    ARE OVER.                   


237
00:17:32,684 --> 00:17:36,520
YOU KNOW, IT'S FUNNY.           
YOU PLAN FOR YOUR LIFE          
TO GO UP ONE ROAD,              


238
00:17:36,589 --> 00:17:41,825
AND WHEN YOU FINALLY GET THERE, 
THE BRIDGE WASHES OUT.          


239
00:17:43,529 --> 00:17:45,629
        WELL, YOU NEVER KNOW.   


240
00:17:45,698 --> 00:17:49,566
        LIFE HAS A STRANGE WAY  
        OF SURPRISING YOU.      


241
00:17:55,307 --> 00:17:58,008
        HEY, LOOK AT THAT.      


242
00:17:58,077 --> 00:18:00,543
         <i> [ Ken ]</i>               
        <i> I'LL BE DAMNED.</i>        


243
00:18:00,612 --> 00:18:05,949
    LIKE I SAID,                
    LIFE IS FULL OF SURPRISES.  


244
00:18:24,003 --> 00:18:28,205
<i>[ Beeping ]</i>                     


245
00:18:28,274 --> 00:18:33,042
KEN WATANABE AND PHIL CAMPBELL, 
FEBRUARY 18, ROLL NUMBER ONE.   


246
00:18:35,046 --> 00:18:37,781
        OKAY. UH--              


247
00:18:37,849 --> 00:18:39,949
NOTHING FANCY, KENNY.           
WE'RE JUST GONNA GO IN THERE,   


248
00:18:40,018 --> 00:18:42,686
    AND WE'RE GONNA SIT DOWN,   
    AND WE'RE GONNA LISTEN      
    TO THE BURNS...<i> </i>            


249
00:18:42,755 --> 00:18:44,688
    TALK ABOUT THEIR SIDE       
    OF THIS TURF WAR.           


250
00:18:44,757 --> 00:18:46,990
THESE GUYS TEND TO              
TALK WITH THEIR GUNS.           
KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?           


251
00:18:47,058 --> 00:18:49,225
YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY         
ABOUT GETTING FANCY FROM ME.    


252
00:18:49,295 --> 00:18:51,928
    DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT, KEN.  
    YOU'LL BE FINE.             


253
00:18:52,998 --> 00:18:54,931
        [ Exhales ]             
        LET'S DO IT.            


254
00:18:58,437 --> 00:19:00,771
[ Ken ]                         
YOU SURE THESE GUYS             
ARE GONNA SHOW?                 


255
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:03,073
[ Phil ]                        
YEAH, THEY'LL BE HERE.          
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.<i> </i>          


256
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:05,676
        OKAY, UM--              


257
00:19:05,745 --> 00:19:08,345
    RIGHT UP THERE.             
    HEAD THERE.                 


258
00:19:08,413 --> 00:19:10,781
[ Ken ]                         
YOU BEEN HANGING WITH           
THE HOMIES, PHIL, HUH?          


259
00:19:19,358 --> 00:19:21,324
        YO! HEY, D-MAC!         


260
00:19:21,393 --> 00:19:24,294
    HEY, D-MAC!                 
    BLEEDERS IN THE HOOD!       


261
00:19:40,012 --> 00:19:41,945
[ Gunfire Resumes ]             


262
00:19:46,418 --> 00:19:50,020
[ Tires Screeching ]            
        I'M HIT!                
         I'M HIT! OH, GOD!      


263
00:19:50,088 --> 00:19:52,722
MY ARM! MY ARM!                 
[ Gunfire Continues ]           


264
00:19:52,791 --> 00:19:55,659
        I'M HIT, MAN! PHIL,     
        GET ME OUT OF HERE, MAN!


265
00:19:55,727 --> 00:19:58,962
            GET ME OUT OF HERE! 
             GET ME OUT OF HERE!
YOU'RE OKAY.                    


266
00:20:01,967 --> 00:20:04,802
        GET ME OUT OF HERE, MAN!
        GET ME OUT OF HERE!     
        GET ME OUT OF HERE!     


267
00:20:10,675 --> 00:20:12,842
<i>INTERESTING UNDERSHIRT, PHIL.</i>   


268
00:21:04,096 --> 00:21:07,230
FLAK JACKET STANDARD ISSUE      
FOR A STREET REPORTER NOW, PHIL?


269
00:21:10,569 --> 00:21:12,869
    I'M DYING FOR A CIGARETTE!  


270
00:21:14,807 --> 00:21:18,108
            <i> HOW THE HELL</i>       
            <i> DID I END UP HERE?</i> 


271
00:21:18,177 --> 00:21:20,544
        YOU REGRET TAKING ON    
        THE JAROD ASSIGNMENT?   


272
00:21:20,612 --> 00:21:24,114
    - I REGRET A LOT OF THINGS. 
    - SUCH AS?                  


273
00:21:26,218 --> 00:21:28,752
I REGRET NOT GOING TO THE PROM. 


274
00:21:28,821 --> 00:21:34,791
    <i> I REGRET LAUGHING</i>          
    <i> AT MY FIRST BOYFRIEND...</i>   


275
00:21:34,860 --> 00:21:37,060
WHEN HE TOLD ME I WAS THE ONE.  


276
00:21:38,497 --> 00:21:41,564
        <i> AND IN THIS INSTANT,</i>   
        <i> I REGRET NOT HAVING...</i> 


277
00:21:41,634 --> 00:21:44,835
        A NICOTINE PATCH        
        THE SIZE OF A DOORMAT.  


278
00:21:49,841 --> 00:21:51,775
                [ Groans ]      
                OH, NO.         


279
00:21:51,844 --> 00:21:55,479
        YOUR ULCER, HUH?        
        AND NO MEDICATION.      


280
00:21:55,547 --> 00:22:00,884
[ Sighs ]                       
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,           
THE FABULOUS SHERLOCK HOLMES.   


281
00:22:04,222 --> 00:22:06,857
            [ Groaning ]        


282
00:22:10,329 --> 00:22:13,597
        LET ME SEE IT, SYDNEY.  


283
00:22:13,666 --> 00:22:18,702
REGRET'S OFTEN BORN OUT         
OF A LACK OF CHOICE, YOU KNOW?  


284
00:22:18,770 --> 00:22:24,074
UNLIKE YOU, SYD,                
I DON'T THINK THAT EVERYTHING   
IS OUT OF MY CONTROL.           


285
00:22:29,748 --> 00:22:32,549
        YOU DO WHEN IT          
        COMES TO YOUR FATHER.   


286
00:22:36,788 --> 00:22:39,990
    PLEASE, DON'T--             
    DON'T MISUNDERSTAND THAT.   


287
00:22:40,058 --> 00:22:42,225
    WHY DON'T YOU JUST SAY IT?  


288
00:22:45,197 --> 00:22:47,664
            I CAVED.            


289
00:22:47,733 --> 00:22:50,200
        I ALWAYS DO AROUND HIM. 


290
00:22:51,971 --> 00:22:54,905
YOU CAN STILL WALK UP           
TO YOUR FATHER AND TELL HIM,    


291
00:22:54,973 --> 00:22:58,074
<i>"DAD, I'M LEAVING."</i>             


292
00:22:59,744 --> 00:23:02,412
                <i> [ Chuckling ]</i>  


293
00:23:02,481 --> 00:23:05,816
    [ Chuckling ]               


294
00:23:08,487 --> 00:23:11,488
        RIGHT. I CAN SEE IT NOW.


295
00:23:11,556 --> 00:23:14,958
        TWO KIDS,               
        A LITTLE YELLOW HOUSE,  


296
00:23:15,027 --> 00:23:17,728
    CHITCHATTING WITH THE GIRLS 
    OVER LATTES AT THE MALL.    


297
00:23:18,930 --> 00:23:21,665
        YOU STILL HAVE A FUTURE,
        MISS PARKER.            


298
00:23:21,733 --> 00:23:25,102
    IT'S A HELL OF A FUTURE,    
    SITTING HERE WAITING        
    TO GET BLOWN TO BITS.       


299
00:23:27,039 --> 00:23:28,738
            [ Chuckles ]        


300
00:23:28,807 --> 00:23:31,274
            [ Laughing ]        


301
00:23:33,444 --> 00:23:38,114
        HERE I AM,              
        TRYING TO COMFORT YOU.  
        [ Laughing Continues ]  


302
00:23:40,618 --> 00:23:44,921
AS IF ANYTHING YOU COULD EVER DO
WOULD GIVE ME COMFORT.          


303
00:23:52,230 --> 00:23:54,397
            IT DID ONCE.        


304
00:23:59,137 --> 00:24:01,070
    YOU ARE ONE HELL            
    OF A THROWER, JAROD.        


305
00:24:01,140 --> 00:24:04,741
IT'S ABOUT UNDERSTANDING        
THE PROJECTILE'S AERODYNAMICS.  


306
00:24:04,809 --> 00:24:09,679
            WELL, ACTUALLY,     
            I JUST CLOSE ONE EYE
            AND LET IT FLY.     


307
00:24:09,748 --> 00:24:12,549
OH.                             
    THAT'S IT. GOOD GAME.       


308
00:24:12,618 --> 00:24:15,051
        I SHOULD'VE WARNED YOU. 
         I DON'T LIKE TO LOSE.  


309
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:18,287
                    GOOD MAN.   
NEXT ROUND'S ON ME.             


310
00:24:18,356 --> 00:24:20,089
        [ Patrons Cheering ]    


311
00:24:20,158 --> 00:24:23,726
        PHIL CERTAINLY IS       
        IN A GOOD MOOD TONIGHT. 


312
00:24:23,795 --> 00:24:28,064
YOU MUST BE VERY PROUD OF ANNIE 
AND PHIL GETTING NOMINATED      
FOR THE KEN WATANABE SEGMENT.   


313
00:24:28,133 --> 00:24:31,401
    YEAH, EVEN STIFFS LIKE PHIL 
    GET LUCKY. IF ONLY          
    GRECIAN FORMULA WERE TALENT.


314
00:24:31,470 --> 00:24:35,271
    <i> AWARDS HELP THE PROMO GUYS,</i>
    <i> I SUPPOSE. THEY ALSO</i>       
    <i> MAKE A NEWS TEAM LAZY.</i>     


315
00:24:35,341 --> 00:24:38,474
    NEWS IS ABOUT BEING HUNGRY. 
    ALWAYS HAS BEEN.            


316
00:24:38,543 --> 00:24:42,145
YOU GUYS GONNA DRINK WATER      
ALL NIGHT, OR ARE YOU COMING    
TO JOIN THE REAL PARTY?         


317
00:24:44,850 --> 00:24:47,951
AND YOU, SMILE.                 


318
00:24:48,020 --> 00:24:51,287
<i>[ Laughing ]</i>                    


319
00:24:52,391 --> 00:24:55,826
    - IS THIS ABOUT KEN?        
    - HE SHOULD BE HERE.        


320
00:24:55,894 --> 00:24:58,527
SOMEBODY FORGOT TO INVITE HIM.  


321
00:24:58,596 --> 00:25:00,130
        [ Inaudible ]           


322
00:25:00,199 --> 00:25:03,700
    <i> HE MUST'VE BEEN VERY PROUD,</i>
    <i> TAKING ONE FOR THE TEAM.</i>   


323
00:25:03,769 --> 00:25:08,805
<i> [ Chris ] KTJE's GOT</i>           
<i> A HELL OF A MEDICAL PACKAGE.</i>   
<i> WATANABE'S ALL RIGHT.</i>          


324
00:25:08,874 --> 00:25:11,808
<i>KEN'S GONNA BE FINE.</i>            
<i>LOOK, EVERYBODY IN</i>              
<i>THIS BUSINESS KNOWS...</i>          


325
00:25:11,877 --> 00:25:14,510
THAT PUTTING YOUR TAIL ON       
THE LINE IS A JOB REQUIREMENT.  


326
00:25:14,579 --> 00:25:19,949
<i>KEN WAS GREEN.</i>                  
<i>HE WAS TOO ZEALOUS,</i>             
<i>AND IT COST HIM.</i>                


327
00:25:20,018 --> 00:25:23,786
IF I'D HAVE KNOWN HOW DANGEROUS 
IT WAS, I NEVER WOULD'VE        
LET HIM GO OUT THERE.           


328
00:25:23,855 --> 00:25:26,322
        I'M SURE YOU WOULDN'T.  


329
00:25:37,035 --> 00:25:41,338
I'M NOT TRYING TO BE A PEST,    
BUT I'VE GOT THE TOWER BREATHING
DOWN MY NECK TO FIND THEM.      


330
00:25:41,407 --> 00:25:46,576
NOW SURELY THERE'S GOT TO BE    
A SWEEPER TEAM SOMEWHERE NEAR   
THE NEW YORK CITY AREA.         


331
00:25:46,645 --> 00:25:50,713
    EXCUSE ME?                  
    WHAT BUSINESS IS IT OF YOURS
    WHAT MY CLEARANCE LEVEL IS? 


332
00:25:50,782 --> 00:25:53,716
NOW, LISTEN. YOU S.I.S. GUYS ARE
REALLY STARTIN' TO TICK ME OFF. 
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>               


333
00:25:53,785 --> 00:25:55,785
            HOLD ON A SECOND.   
            JUST HOLD ON.       


334
00:25:55,854 --> 00:25:58,587
            - BROOTS!           
            - IT'S ME.          


335
00:25:58,656 --> 00:26:00,824
DON'T BOTHER TRYING TO TRACE ME.


336
00:26:00,892 --> 00:26:04,027
    - I'VE SCRAMBLED            
      THE SOURCE SIGNAL.        
    - JAROD?                    


337
00:26:06,598 --> 00:26:10,400
            I'VE BEEN TRYING    
            TO CONTACT SYDNEY.  
    JOIN THE PARTY.             


338
00:26:10,469 --> 00:26:14,337
HE AND MISS PARKER WENT LOOKING 
FOR YOU TWO DAYS AGO. WE        
HAVEN'T HEARD FROM THEM SINCE.  


339
00:26:14,405 --> 00:26:18,841
    SHE'S TOO PERSISTENT        
    FOR HER OWN GOOD. YOU'RE    
    GOING TO HAVE TO FIND THEM. 


340
00:26:18,910 --> 00:26:21,043
    YOU DON'T KNOW HOW PEACEFUL 
    IT'S BEEN HERE WITHOUT HER. 


341
00:26:21,112 --> 00:26:23,045
    WOULD IT BE MORE PEACEFUL   
    WORKING FOR RAINES?         


342
00:26:23,114 --> 00:26:27,851
        MR. RAINES? NO.         
TAKE DOWN THIS ADDRESS.         


343
00:26:27,920 --> 00:26:32,055
    1811 NORTH BUSHNELL STREET, 
    THE BRONX.                  


344
00:26:43,868 --> 00:26:47,103
                    [ Crying ]  


345
00:26:47,172 --> 00:26:50,173
        [ Soft Chattering ]     


346
00:27:09,694 --> 00:27:11,694
    MISS PARKER?                


347
00:27:45,663 --> 00:27:48,431
TELL ME AGAIN                   
HOW MY MOTHER DIED.             


348
00:27:56,074 --> 00:27:58,007
        STOP TORTURING YOURSELF.


349
00:27:58,076 --> 00:28:00,676
I KNOW IT WASN'T SUICIDE.       


350
00:28:02,914 --> 00:28:05,681
WAS SHE MURDERED BECAUSE        
OF THE RESCUED CHILDREN?        


351
00:28:08,419 --> 00:28:12,054
    - I DON'T KNOW.             
    - WAS IT MY FATHER?         


352
00:28:14,159 --> 00:28:20,129
MISS PARKER,                    
I KNOW ABOUT YOUR MOTHER'S LIFE,
NOT ABOUT HER DEATH.            


353
00:28:20,198 --> 00:28:22,165
        <i> SHE WAS A KIND WOMAN,</i>  


354
00:28:22,234 --> 00:28:27,770
A DRIVING FORCE AT THE CENTRE   
IN THOSE DAYS WHEN              
IT WAS STILL INVOLVED IN...     


355
00:28:29,641 --> 00:28:31,641
        ALTRUISTIC PROJECTS.    


356
00:28:33,978 --> 00:28:38,748
I CAN'T BELIEVE THE CENTRE      
WAS EVER INVOLVED WITH          
ANYTHING POSITIVE.              


357
00:28:38,816 --> 00:28:44,654
WE HELPED FOUR COUNTRIES BECOME 
DEMOCRACIES DURING THE COLD WAR.


358
00:28:44,722 --> 00:28:50,159
<i>WE BROUGHT THE SIDES TOGETHER</i>   
<i>FOR THE KOREAN PEACE ACCORD.</i>    


359
00:28:50,228 --> 00:28:55,065
AND RUMOR HAS IT THAT WE EVEN   
HELPED DESIGN THE POPEMOBILE.   


360
00:28:56,801 --> 00:29:00,736
    <i> THE CENTRE</i>                 
    <i> SAVED THOUSANDS OF LIVES--</i> 


361
00:29:00,806 --> 00:29:06,475
        LIVES THAT THEY         
        LATER RECLAIMED,        


362
00:29:06,544 --> 00:29:10,479
        AS IT TURNED OUT,       
        IN OTHER WAYS.          


363
00:29:10,548 --> 00:29:14,417
WHY DIDN'T YOU LEAVE            
WHEN THINGS TURNED?             


364
00:29:15,553 --> 00:29:18,554
            <i> THERE WERE OTHERS</i>  
            <i> WHOSE WELFARE...</i>   


365
00:29:18,623 --> 00:29:23,759
    WAS OF MORE CONCERN TO ME   
    THAN MY OWN.                


366
00:29:23,828 --> 00:29:25,595
        JAROD.                  


367
00:29:25,664 --> 00:29:29,131
HE'S NOT VERY DIFFERENT FROM US,
YOU KNOW?                       


368
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:35,171
        <i> WE'D ALL HAVE TAKEN</i>    
        <i> VERY DIFFERENT PATHS...</i>


369
00:29:36,274 --> 00:29:38,608
            HAD WE HAD OUR WAY. 


370
00:29:45,183 --> 00:29:47,884
    HERE YOU GO.                
    PASS THE BALL, MAN.         
    [ Chattering ]              


371
00:29:50,455 --> 00:29:54,123
    - BOO-YA!                   
    - EXCUSE ME. EXCUSE ME.     


372
00:29:55,393 --> 00:29:58,294
    I THINK THAT WAS TRAVELING. 


373
00:29:58,363 --> 00:30:02,465
        YOU MUST BE CRAZY,      
        STUPID OR BOTH.         


374
00:30:02,534 --> 00:30:06,903
NO, NO. AFTER YOU LIFTED        
YOUR PIVOT FOOT, YOU TOOK MORE  
THAN THE ALLOTTED TWO STEPS,    


375
00:30:06,972 --> 00:30:08,904
        AS OUTLINED IN          
        THE OFFICIAL RULE BOOK. 


376
00:30:08,973 --> 00:30:13,609
        MMM.                    
                PIZZA?          


377
00:30:13,678 --> 00:30:16,245
THANK YOU, ANYWAY,              
BUT IT ALREADY COMES PRESLICED. 


378
00:30:17,482 --> 00:30:19,582
                HELP YOURSELVES.


379
00:30:19,651 --> 00:30:22,818
WHAT, YOU GOT A DEATH WISH      
OR SOMETHING, MAN?              
            NOT THAT I KNOW OF. 


380
00:30:22,887 --> 00:30:25,087
DIDN'T YOUR MAMA EVER TELL YOU  
THAT WHITE PEOPLE SHOULDN'T...  


381
00:30:25,156 --> 00:30:27,089
GO WALKING THROUGH              
OTHER PEOPLE'S NEIGHBORHOODS?   


382
00:30:27,158 --> 00:30:31,194
    WELL, I NEVER ACTUALLY      
    KNEW MY MOTHER,             
    SO I GUESS THE ANSWER IS NO.


383
00:30:31,262 --> 00:30:34,964
    MY NAME'S JAROD CRANE.      
    I'M WITH<i> CHANNEL 43 NEWS.</i>   


384
00:30:35,033 --> 00:30:37,500
        I'M LOOKING FOR A D-MAC.


385
00:30:40,272 --> 00:30:43,139
YOU GONNA PUT HIM ON TV?        
            QUITE POSSIBLY, YES.


386
00:30:44,776 --> 00:30:48,811
I'M D-MAC.                      
            NICE TO MEET YOU.   


387
00:30:52,418 --> 00:30:54,684
<i>OW! HE'S GOT GAME.</i>              
<i>THE BOY'S GOT SOME GAME.</i>        


388
00:30:54,753 --> 00:30:57,487
[ Chattering ]                  


389
00:30:59,024 --> 00:31:01,658
HEY, MAN, THAT CAMERA GUY       
SHOULDN'T HAVE BEEN THERE.      


390
00:31:01,727 --> 00:31:04,628
        TELL ME WHAT HAPPENED.  
<i>A MAN HITS MY CELL PHONE.</i>       


391
00:31:04,697 --> 00:31:08,699
HE MUST'VE PAID SOMEBODY        
OFF TO GET THE NUMBER.          
SOUNDED WHITE.                  


392
00:31:08,767 --> 00:31:12,503
TELLS ME HE WANTS               
TO TALK ABOUT THE TURF WARS.    
SOUNDED COOL TO ME.             


393
00:31:12,571 --> 00:31:16,573
THIS WHITE MAN THAT CALLED YOU, 
IS THAT UNUSUAL?                


394
00:31:19,245 --> 00:31:21,244
YOU REALLY DIDN'T HAVE          
NO MOTHER, DID YOU?             


395
00:31:25,584 --> 00:31:27,518
I NEVER KNEW MY OLD LADY EITHER.


396
00:31:29,154 --> 00:31:32,189
<i>LATER I HEARD WORD THE BLEEDERS</i> 
<i>GOT THE SAME CALL.</i>              


397
00:31:32,257 --> 00:31:36,660
<i>THEY SHOW UP, AND BOOM, BOOM,</i>   
<i>THE FIREWORKS STARTED.</i>          


398
00:31:37,863 --> 00:31:39,863
        DO YOU REMEMBER WHAT DAY
        YOU GOT THIS CALL?      


399
00:31:39,932 --> 00:31:43,567
I DON'T KNOW.                   
HEY, DUANE, MAN,                
BRING MY DAY RUNNER.            


400
00:31:46,472 --> 00:31:50,774
WE'RE BANGERS, NOT CAVEMEN.     
THANKS, MAN.                    


401
00:31:50,842 --> 00:31:55,546
OKAY, HERE YOU GO. FEBRUARY 18, 
AT ABOUT 8:00 AT NIGHT.         


402
00:31:59,418 --> 00:32:01,351
        COULD YOU TELL ME       
        YOUR CELL PHONE NUMBER? 


403
00:32:08,027 --> 00:32:10,727
                <i> [ Chattering ]</i> 


404
00:32:47,866 --> 00:32:50,667
        [ Crying ]              


405
00:32:56,075 --> 00:32:58,708
TAKE MISS PARKER UPSTAIRS.      
                    YES, SIR.   


406
00:33:00,479 --> 00:33:03,513
YOU GET SOME REST NOW.          


407
00:33:03,582 --> 00:33:08,118
IF YOU EVER WANT TO TALK TO ME, 
I'M ALWAYS HERE.                
            [ Crying Continues ]


408
00:33:08,187 --> 00:33:11,788
OKAY?                           
            THANK YOU, SYDNEY.  


409
00:33:33,111 --> 00:33:35,112
                        SYDNEY? 


410
00:33:36,482 --> 00:33:42,052
WHY IS EVERYONE WEARING BLACK?  
HOW COME YOU'RE SO SAD?         


411
00:33:42,120 --> 00:33:47,090
    WE'RE REMEMBERING SOMEONE   
    WHO HAS LEFT US, JAROD.     


412
00:33:47,159 --> 00:33:49,960
                IS IT THE WOMAN 
                THAT GOT SHOT   
                IN THE ELEVATOR?


413
00:33:50,028 --> 00:33:52,029
MISS PARKER'S MOTHER, ISN'T IT? 


414
00:33:52,097 --> 00:33:56,666
DON'T YOU EVER SPEAK OF THAT    
TO ANYONE EVER AGAIN,           
UNDERSTAND?                     


415
00:34:02,674 --> 00:34:04,675
            [ Groans ]          


416
00:34:19,592 --> 00:34:21,558
        I COULD'VE SAVED HIM.   


417
00:34:21,627 --> 00:34:23,627
WHO?                            


418
00:34:25,097 --> 00:34:27,197
                    JAROD.      


419
00:34:27,266 --> 00:34:31,001
            HE SHOULD HAVE LIVED
            A NORMAL LIFE.      


420
00:34:31,070 --> 00:34:33,904
THEY WOULD'VE KILLED YOU.       
                [ Chuckles ]    


421
00:34:33,972 --> 00:34:39,542
        YOU CAN'T KILL SOMEONE  
        WHO'S ALREADY DEAD.     


422
00:34:39,611 --> 00:34:41,678
                <i> [ Shuddering ]</i> 


423
00:34:55,761 --> 00:34:58,628
                YOU DO REMEMBER.


424
00:35:08,106 --> 00:35:10,941
YOU BROKE INTO MY EDIT FILE     
AND STOLE FOOTAGE?              


425
00:35:11,009 --> 00:35:13,210
    "BORROWED" IS MORE LIKE IT. 


426
00:35:13,278 --> 00:35:16,079
            AND I DID IT        
            FOR KEN WATANABE.   
YOU LOST ME.                    


427
00:35:16,148 --> 00:35:18,848
                KEN WAS SET UP. 
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?     


428
00:35:18,917 --> 00:35:22,752
    WHAT HAPPENED TO KEN        
    HAPPENED BECAUSE PHIL       
    IS DESPERATE FOR RATINGS.   


429
00:35:22,821 --> 00:35:24,921
I-I-I DON'T BUY THAT.           


430
00:35:24,990 --> 00:35:27,924
                    BUY IT.     


431
00:35:27,993 --> 00:35:33,730
WHY ELSE WOULD PHIL HAVE BEEN   
WEARING A BULLETPROOF VEST      
THE NIGHT THAT KEN WAS SHOT?    


432
00:35:40,206 --> 00:35:42,338
YOU ACTUALLY THINK PHIL WOULD DO
SOMETHING LIKE THAT?            


433
00:35:42,407 --> 00:35:45,609
            I'M CERTAIN OF IT.  
            ANNIE, YOU KNOW HIM.


434
00:35:45,677 --> 00:35:48,978
YOU'VE SEEN THE KIND OF PRESSURE
THAT PHIL HAS BEEN UNDER        
TO GET BACK ON TOP.             


435
00:35:49,047 --> 00:35:51,314
    YEAH, BUT TO RISK           
    SOMEBODY ELSE'S LIFE.       


436
00:35:51,383 --> 00:35:53,316
    HE'S A DESPERATE MAN, ANNIE.


437
00:35:53,385 --> 00:35:55,852
    HE WAS THE KING OF THE HILL,
    AND NOW HE'S ON HIS WAY OUT.


438
00:35:55,921 --> 00:36:01,257
        ANNIE, I NEED YOUR HELP 
        TO STOP HIM.            


439
00:36:08,934 --> 00:36:12,069
<i>HELLO, DAVE. THIS IS JAROD.</i>     


440
00:36:12,137 --> 00:36:14,904
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE TO           
COME TO WORK FOR CHANNEL 43?    


441
00:36:14,973 --> 00:36:19,309
UH-HUH. YOU CAN TELL YOUR WIFE  
YOU'VE GOT A JOB.               


442
00:36:19,378 --> 00:36:21,745
<i>♪♪ [ Rap, Indistinct ]</i>          


443
00:36:25,651 --> 00:36:27,384
                LIGHTS.         


444
00:36:28,420 --> 00:36:31,855
<i>♪♪ [ Continues ]</i>                


445
00:36:31,924 --> 00:36:34,223
                CAMERA.         


446
00:36:40,666 --> 00:36:45,502
    HELLO, ANNIE. I'M SETTING UP
    A VERY SPECIAL SCREENING    
    IN CHRIS'S OFFICE.          


447
00:36:45,571 --> 00:36:50,040
I WANT YOU TO DO ME A FAVOR.    
MAKE SURE THE GENERAL MANAGER   
IS THERE.                       


448
00:36:51,644 --> 00:36:54,010
                    ACTION.     


449
00:36:55,313 --> 00:36:57,314
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>PHIL.</i>                           


450
00:36:58,917 --> 00:37:02,418
CHRIS JUST GOT WORD             
OF A SUMMIT GOING DOWN          
BETWEEN TWO RIVAL GANGS.        


451
00:37:02,487 --> 00:37:06,289
HE THINKS IT'S GOING TO MAKE    
A TERRIFIC FOLLOW-UP            
TO THE KEN WATANABE SEGMENT.    


452
00:37:06,357 --> 00:37:08,357
    CHRIS TIPPED YOU ON THIS?   


453
00:37:08,426 --> 00:37:13,430
HIS SNITCH SAID THERE           
COULD BE FIREWORKS,             
AND FIREWORKS MEAN RATINGS.     


454
00:37:13,498 --> 00:37:15,499
                    LET'S GO.   


455
00:37:26,111 --> 00:37:28,078
PHIL, WHY DON'T                 
YOU TEST YOUR HEADSET?          


456
00:37:28,146 --> 00:37:30,713
            CHECK, ONE, TWO.    


457
00:37:34,753 --> 00:37:37,387
SO, WHERE SHALL WE SET UP?      


458
00:37:38,456 --> 00:37:40,690
        OVER HERE.              


459
00:37:40,759 --> 00:37:44,661
    WE CAN COVER THE DOOR,      
    STAY IN THE SHADOWS.        


460
00:37:46,498 --> 00:37:49,599
        UH, JAROD.              
        SOMETHING DOESN'T FEEL  
        RIGHT ABOUT THIS.       


461
00:37:49,667 --> 00:37:51,901
WELL, IT'S A PRETTY SCARY PLACE.


462
00:37:51,970 --> 00:37:54,837
THAT AND THE FACT THAT          
KEN WATANABE WAS SHOT           
JUST OUTSIDE OF THAT DOOR.      


463
00:37:54,906 --> 00:37:56,840
THAT MIGHT HAVE SOMETHING       
TO DO WITH IT.                  


464
00:37:56,908 --> 00:38:00,577
<i>BUT PUTTING OUR TAIL</i>            
<i>ON THE LINE-- IT'S PART</i>         
<i>OF THE JOB, ISN'T IT?</i>           


465
00:38:06,651 --> 00:38:10,319
            OKAY, JAROD. JAROD? 


466
00:38:16,261 --> 00:38:19,295
            JAROD!              
                <i> [ Door Opens ]</i> 


467
00:38:19,364 --> 00:38:22,432
-<i> [ Man ] BURNS IN THE HOUSE!</i>   
-<i> [ Man #2 ] WORD!</i>              


468
00:38:22,501 --> 00:38:25,535
                [ Men Shouting ]


469
00:38:25,604 --> 00:38:28,538
    - BRING YOUR PUNK-ASSES OUT!
    -<i> LET'S GO!</i>                 


470
00:38:28,606 --> 00:38:32,142
- DON'T WAIT FOR THEIR ASSES.   
- JAROD, WHERE ARE YOU?         


471
00:38:32,210 --> 00:38:34,444
<i>[ Jarod On Headset ]</i>            
<i>ABOVE YOU.</i>                      


472
00:38:34,513 --> 00:38:37,514
<i>[ Phil ]</i>                        
<i>THIS IS NOT GOOD.</i>               


473
00:38:37,582 --> 00:38:39,549
            <i> [ On Headset ]</i>     
            <i> IT'S OKAY. I'VE GOT</i>
            <i> YOU IN MY SIGHTS.</i>  


474
00:38:39,617 --> 00:38:42,352
<i>SMILE, PHIL. IT'S SHOWTIME.</i>     


475
00:38:45,690 --> 00:38:48,591
    ANNIE, WHY IS               
    THE GENERAL MANAGER HERE?   


476
00:38:48,660 --> 00:38:50,660
I THINK YOU HAVE                
A MEETING WITH HIM.             


477
00:38:57,068 --> 00:38:59,402
MR. FERREN, WHAT A SURPRISE.    


478
00:38:59,471 --> 00:39:01,471
    NICE TO SEE YOU AGAIN,      
    MR. FERREN.                 


479
00:39:01,540 --> 00:39:03,606
        SHOW'S ABOUT            
        TO BEGIN, GENTLEMEN.    
        PLEASE, TAKE YOUR SEATS.


480
00:39:03,675 --> 00:39:06,909
        I'M INTRIGUED, ROCKWELL.
        THIS MUST BE SOME SHOW  
        YOU'VE PUT TOGETHER.    


481
00:39:06,978 --> 00:39:09,912
YES, SIR. THE BEST.             


482
00:39:11,382 --> 00:39:13,884
                [ Men Shouting ]


483
00:39:20,426 --> 00:39:23,460
    -<i> [ Man On TV ] WHAT?</i>       
    - WHAT YOU WANT WITH ME?    


484
00:39:23,529 --> 00:39:25,462
                WHAT'S UP, FOOL?
<i>[ Mr. Ferren ]</i>                  
<i>WHAT IS THIS, A GANG FIGHT?</i>     


485
00:39:25,531 --> 00:39:28,498
        WANT SOME OF THIS, HUH? 
        YOU WANT SOME OF THIS?  
<i>[ Chris ] IS THAT PHIL?</i>         


486
00:39:28,567 --> 00:39:32,101
                <i> WHAT YOU GOT?</i>  
JAROD, THESE GUYS               
ARE GONNA KILL EACH OTHER.      


487
00:39:32,170 --> 00:39:35,705
<i>[ Jarod ] IT'LL BE GREAT TV.</i>    
        YOU CALL ME HERE        
        TO THREATEN MY ASS?     


488
00:39:36,908 --> 00:39:40,277
THIS IS ON YOU, DOG.            
DEAL OR DIE.                    


489
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:45,181
            [ Chattering ]      


490
00:39:45,250 --> 00:39:48,584
    <i> THIS IS GREAT STUFF, PHIL.</i> 
    <i> GET CLOSER SO WE CAN</i>       
    <i> PICK UP SOUND.</i>             


491
00:39:48,653 --> 00:39:51,721
I'VE GOT NO COVER HERE,         
YOU IDIOT!                      


492
00:39:52,891 --> 00:39:54,891
I'M GETTING OUT OF HERE.        


493
00:39:54,960 --> 00:39:57,360
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>DON'T LEAVE NOW, PHIL.</i>          
<i>YOU'RE GONNA MISS THE STORY.</i>    


494
00:39:57,429 --> 00:39:59,595
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>YOU WANT SOME OF THIS? HUH?</i>     
<i>YOU WANT SOME OF THIS?</i>          


495
00:39:59,664 --> 00:40:02,798
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>OR MAYBE YOU ARE THE STORY.</i>     
        [ Banging ]             


496
00:40:02,867 --> 00:40:05,768
WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?          
<i>[ Banging ]</i>                     


497
00:40:08,273 --> 00:40:11,440
-HE'S MINE!                     
-JAROD, HELP ME! JAROD, HELP ME!


498
00:40:11,509 --> 00:40:14,377
<i>JAROD!</i>                          
<i>[ Men Chattering ]</i>              


499
00:40:15,447 --> 00:40:17,380
        JAROD, HELP ME!         
    YEAH!                       


500
00:40:17,449 --> 00:40:19,316
    THIS IS GREAT.              
     THIS IS GREAT. KEEP IT UP. 


501
00:40:19,384 --> 00:40:23,819
LOOK WHAT WE GOT HERE, FELLAS.  
UH-HUH.                         


502
00:40:26,558 --> 00:40:28,859
    DAVE, READY TO GO CITYWIDE? 


503
00:40:28,927 --> 00:40:31,394
GET READY, SEATTLE.             


504
00:40:31,463 --> 00:40:34,764
        [ Men Whooping ]        


505
00:40:34,833 --> 00:40:38,401
- SO WHAT WE GONNA DO           
  WITH THIS WHITE PUNK?         
- [ Men Grumbling ]             


506
00:40:38,470 --> 00:40:41,171
I SAY WE BURY HIS SORRY ASS     
RIGHT WHERE HE STANDS.          


507
00:40:41,240 --> 00:40:45,074
[ Clicking ]                    
        [ Grumbling Continues ] 


508
00:40:45,143 --> 00:40:47,577
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>HEY, IT'S ON EVERY CHANNEL.</i>     


509
00:40:47,645 --> 00:40:49,746
<i>[ Man #2 ]</i>                      
<i>SOMETHING'S GOING ON.</i>           
<i>LOOK AT THIS.</i>                   


510
00:40:49,814 --> 00:40:53,249
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>THIS IS GONNA BE A GREAT PIECE,</i> 
<i>PHIL. JUST KEEP THEM TALKING.</i>   


511
00:40:53,318 --> 00:40:55,751
    <i> [ Men Chattering On TV ]</i>   


512
00:40:55,820 --> 00:40:57,854
            THIS GUY'S GONNA    
            SHOOT ME.           


513
00:40:57,922 --> 00:41:00,856
    - JUST LIKE KEN WATANABE?   
    - WHAT?                     


514
00:41:00,925 --> 00:41:03,859
<i>JAROD, COME DOWN HERE!</i>          


515
00:41:03,928 --> 00:41:06,663
        WHAT'S UP? YOU GONNA DO 
        THE DEED OR NOT?        
        'CAUSE IF YOU'RE NOT--  


516
00:41:06,732 --> 00:41:10,366
    [ Guns Cocking ]            
    NO, NO, YOU CAN'T SHOOT ME! 
     NO, YOU CAN'T!             


517
00:41:10,435 --> 00:41:13,035
    HE'S GOT A TV CAMERA ON YOU.


518
00:41:13,104 --> 00:41:16,406
CAMERAS.                        
THEY CAN DO WONDERFUL THINGS.   


519
00:41:16,475 --> 00:41:20,477
    BUT KEN WATANABE'S CAMERA   
    COULDN'T STOP HIM           
    FROM GETTING SHOT.          


520
00:41:20,545 --> 00:41:23,212
        I DIDN'T KNOW THERE WAS 
        GONNA BE SHOOTING.      


521
00:41:23,281 --> 00:41:25,482
BUT YOU DID KNOW THAT A RIVAL   
GANG WAS GOING TO BE THERE,     


522
00:41:25,550 --> 00:41:27,484
    BECAUSE YOU TIPPED THEM OFF,


523
00:41:27,553 --> 00:41:30,119
<i>AND THAT'S WHY YOU WORE</i>         
<i>A BULLETPROOF VEST.</i>             


524
00:41:30,188 --> 00:41:32,121
            I TIPPED THEM OFF.  
            OKAY, OKAY!         


525
00:41:32,190 --> 00:41:34,490
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>YOU KNEW YOU WERE PUTTING</i>       
<i>KEN WATANABE IN DANGER,</i>         


526
00:41:34,559 --> 00:41:38,061
    BUT YOU DIDN'T CARE BECAUSE 
    ALL YOU CARE ABOUT          
    IS GETTING THE STORY.       


527
00:41:38,129 --> 00:41:40,296
        YES! PLEASE, HELP ME!   


528
00:41:40,365 --> 00:41:42,298
<i>I CAN'T DO THAT, PHIL.</i>          


529
00:41:42,367 --> 00:41:44,934
    IT'S RATINGS AT ALL COSTS.  


530
00:41:45,003 --> 00:41:49,372
    LIKE YOU ALWAYS SAY,        
    "IF IT BLEEDS, IT LEADS."   


531
00:41:49,440 --> 00:41:53,009
    I SET HIM UP. I SET HIM UP. 
     I SET IT UP, OKAY?         


532
00:41:55,380 --> 00:41:59,382
YOU GOT WHAT YOU NEED, BRO?     
<i>IT'S A SLAM DUNK.</i>               


533
00:41:59,450 --> 00:42:02,084
            I GOT EVERYTHING    
             I NEED RIGHT HERE. 


534
00:42:02,153 --> 00:42:05,288
        [ Men Laughing ]        


535
00:42:05,357 --> 00:42:08,191
"I SET HIM UP! I SET HIM UP!"   


536
00:42:11,162 --> 00:42:15,398
        [ Voices, Indistinct ]  


537
00:42:15,467 --> 00:42:17,733
    THAT WAS THE MONEY SHOT     
    YOU'VE ALL BEEN WAITING FOR.


538
00:42:17,802 --> 00:42:21,204
     JAROD CRANE,               
    <i> CHANNEL 43 NEWS,</i> REPORTING.


539
00:42:24,509 --> 00:42:26,909
        [ Crowd Murmuring ]     


540
00:42:30,815 --> 00:42:33,850
    I'M HOLDING YOU RESPONSIBLE 
    FOR THIS, MR. ROCKWELL.     


541
00:42:33,918 --> 00:42:37,353
FORGET THE LIABILITY THIS       
STATION FACES IN LIGHT OF THIS. 


542
00:42:37,422 --> 00:42:39,222
        YOU RUINED A MAN'S LIFE.


543
00:42:39,291 --> 00:42:41,223
                    SIR, I--    
SAVE IT. SAVE IT.               


544
00:42:41,292 --> 00:42:45,495
YOU WANT A NEWS FLASH, CHRIS?   
YOU'RE FIRED.                   


545
00:42:45,564 --> 00:42:48,097
            [ All Murmuring ]   


546
00:43:12,156 --> 00:43:14,491
<i>OH, MY GOD.</i>                     


547
00:43:26,204 --> 00:43:28,938
    MISS PARKER! SYDNEY!        


548
00:43:31,409 --> 00:43:35,145
        - IT CAN'T BE.          
        - SYDNEY! MISS P.!      


549
00:43:35,213 --> 00:43:39,949
    BROOTS! YOU MORON!          
<i>MISS PARKER!</i>                    


550
00:43:40,018 --> 00:43:42,418
<i>DOWN HERE!</i>                      


551
00:43:44,055 --> 00:43:46,322
    SYDNEY, WAKE UP.            


552
00:43:51,863 --> 00:43:53,863
                [ Chattering ]  


553
00:43:56,434 --> 00:43:58,368
                    HI.         


554
00:43:58,436 --> 00:44:01,003
            HOW'RE YOU DOING?   
            I FIGURED YOU GUYS  
            MIGHT BE HUNGRY.    


555
00:44:01,072 --> 00:44:03,473
    FORGET THAT.                
    DOES ANYBODY SMOKE? SMOKE?  


556
00:44:03,541 --> 00:44:05,541
    NO.                         
NO.                             


557
00:44:08,813 --> 00:44:12,114
HI. UH, CAN I--                 


558
00:44:12,183 --> 00:44:14,183
    THANK YOU.                  


559
00:44:27,465 --> 00:44:30,566
BOY, IT'S LUCKY                 
I FOUND YOU GUYS.               


560
00:44:30,635 --> 00:44:32,568
OTHERWISE,                      
YOU WOULD'VE BEEN TOAST.        


561
00:44:35,373 --> 00:44:39,709
<i>YOU CAN PUT ANY FANTASY ABOUT ME</i>
<i>THANKING YOU TO REST, BROOTS.</i>   


562
00:44:39,778 --> 00:44:41,710
        [ Huffs ]               


563
00:44:41,780 --> 00:44:44,180
        RIGHT.                  
        [ Chuckles ]            


564
00:44:44,249 --> 00:44:48,384
    SO, WHAT DID YOU GUYS       
    TALK ABOUT ALL THIS TIME?   


565
00:44:50,555 --> 00:44:52,989
            NOTHING.            


566
00:44:53,058 --> 00:44:55,058
                <i> NOTHING AT ALL.</i>


567
00:44:59,230 --> 00:45:01,831
[ Huffs ]                       
YOU'RE WELCOME.                 


568
00:45:08,340 --> 00:45:12,008
THIS IS GREAT.                  
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO THANK YOU.  


569
00:45:12,076 --> 00:45:14,444
        <i> I MEAN, YOU BUILT</i>      
        <i> THIS HARNESS FOR ME...</i> 
        [ Chuckling ]           


570
00:45:14,513 --> 00:45:16,545
        <i> AND GOT ME MY JOB BACK</i> 
        <i> AT THE STATION.</i>        


571
00:45:16,614 --> 00:45:19,048
YOU'VE GOT TO PROMISE ME THAT   
THIS WILL NEVER MAKE THE AIR.   


572
00:45:19,117 --> 00:45:20,883
                    I PROMISE.  


573
00:45:20,952 --> 00:45:26,255
